A foreign spouse marrying under common-law won’t receive a legal separation unless there is a separation agreement (or 6 years have passed since cese de convivencia). Under Spanish law though, you can apply for divorce FREE OF CHARGE if you are a Spanish citizen or the husband formerly lived in Spain. Self-employment is on the rise in Andorra. Unfortunately, with a growing work force, there are more employee rights to consider and it’s obvious that this could lead to some difficult situations.

In order to start the divorce procedure, you have to file a petition for divorce. The filing has to contain three pieces, first you must mention the reason of why you filed the divorce, then all the related background information like family life, finances and kids. Finally, you must also specify the divorce process. It has to meet memorial requirements and after it has been signed, a juror has to approve it.

This type of divorce can be achieved relatively quickly and inexpensively since the parties simply need to sign an agreement.
